Privacy Policy for Alfred's List

Effective Date: July 6th, 2025

Alfred's List respects your privacy. This Privacy Policy describes how we collect, use, and protect your personal information when you use our mobile application.

1. Information We Collect
We collect the following information from users of our app:

Email Address – This is used to create and manage your account, and for communication purposes related to the app.
We do not collect any other personal data such as location, photos, camera access, health data, or financial information.

2. How We Use Your Information
We use your email address to:

Create and manage your account
Send you important updates or service-related messages
Provide customer support
We do not sell, rent, or share your personal information with third parties for marketing purposes.

3. Account Management
You may delete your account at any time within the app or by contacting us at [Insert Contact Email]. Upon deletion, your personal information will be removed from our active databases.

4. Data Security
We implement reasonable security measures to protect your personal information from unauthorized access, alteration, or disclosure. However, no method of transmission over the internet or mobile device is 100% secure.

5. Children’s Privacy
Alfred's List is not intended for children under the age of 13. We do not knowingly collect personal information from children under 13.

6. Changes to This Policy
We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. If we make significant changes, we will notify you within the app or via email.

7. Contact Us
If you have any questions about this Privacy Policy, please contact us at:

Email: gabrielyutabelmont@gmail.com

Legal Jurisdiction

This policy is governed by the laws of the Commonwealth of Massachusetts and the United States.
